== Transportation == ;Rail * To the Sakae-side venue: A 2-minute walk from [[:en:Utsubuna Station|Utsubuna Station]] on the [[:en:Minobu Line|Minobu Line]]. Temporary trains operate during the festival, similar to those for the {{ill|Shinmei Fireworks Festival|ja|神明の花火大会|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinmei Fireworks Festival|qq=}}. Food stalls offering classics like yakisoba, takoyaki, and jumbo sausages are present, but additional snacks and drinks can be purchased at nearby convenience stores (e.g., a Daily Yamazaki) or local shops. * To the Mutsumiai-side main venue: A 10-minute walk from Utsubuna Station, crossing the {{ill|Nanbu Bridge (Fuji River)|ja|南部橋 (富士川)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nanbu Bridge (Fuji River)|qq=}}. While the 2011 Completion tier 2]][[Category: of a new bridge widened the pedestrian path, traffic restrictions may apply during busy times. * Additional services: Temporary trains or extended train schedules are available between [[:en:Fuji Station|Fuji Station]], Utsubuna Station, and [[:en:Minobu Station|Minobu Station]]. Temporary train schedules are typically not listed in commercial timetables but are announced via [[:en:Central Japan Railway Company|JR Central]]'s official website or flyers distributed around the same time as the Shinmei Fireworks Festival announcements. ;Car * Guidance signs are posted along [[:en:Japan National Route 52|National Route 52 (Japan)]] and {{ill|Shizuoka-Yamanashi Prefectural Route 10|ja|静岡県道・山梨県道10号富士川身延線|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shizuoka-Yamanashi Prefectural Route 10|qq=}}. Parking is available near the main venue on the Mutsumiai side but requires using designated lots due to traffic restrictions. Parking areas include locations near Utsubuna Station and along the Fuji River embankments. Note that the parking lot at Utsubuna Station, usually free, charges fees on the festival day.
